### Customer's addresses [/api/v1/storefront/customers/me/addresses]

#### List all addresses, if lat and lng provided, it will attach the distance from that location on each address [GET /api/v2/storefront/customers/me/addresses]

@todo: there is also a v1 namespaced endpoint for retrieving this. What is the difference?

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "lat": "13.730711000000",
            "lng": "100.594267000000"
        }
 
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "data": [
                {
                    "address_id": 9909,
                    "type": "others",
                    "building_name": "SSP Building",
                    "room_number": "0",
                    "floor_number": "22",
                    "address1": "Ekkamai rd",
                    "address2": null,
                    "district": "",
                    "city": "Bangkok",
                    "postcode": null,
                    "directions": "Call when you arrive in the foyer",
                    "address_label": null,
                    "latitude": "13.720711000000",
                    "longitude": "100.584267000000",
                    "area_id": null,
                    "geolocation_source": null,
                    "formatted": "SSP Building\nFloor #22\nEkkamai rd\nBangkok",
                    "distance": 20.23
                }
            ]
        }

